cups-pk-helper
==============

http://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/cups-pk-helper

cups-pk-helper is a PolicyKit helper to configure cups with fine-grained
privileges.

For example, it's possible to let users enable/disable printers without
requiring a password, while still requiring a password for editing printer
settings. The full list of policies is described in
src/org.opensuse.cupspkhelper.mechanism.policy.in.

You may download updates to the package from:

   https://www.freedesktop.org/software/cups-pk-helper/releases/


Installation
============

You can use one of these commands to install cups-pk-helper:

DESTDIR=/path/to/staging/area meson install
meson install --destdir=/path/to/staging/area

Or just "meson install" if you've set "prefix" option before.


How to report bugs
==================

Please report found issues and feature requests in freedesktop.org's GitLab:

   https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/cups-pk-helper/cups-pk-helper/-/issues

You will need to create an account for yourself.

Please read the following page on how to prepare a useful bug report:

   https://bugs.freedesktop.org/page.cgi?id=bug-writing.html

Please read the HACKING file for information on where to send changes or
bugfixes for this package.


Code of Conduct
===============

cups-pk-helper project has adopted Code of Conduct of freedesktop.org.
In short, it requires everyone participating in discussion on freedesktop.org
to engage in good faith, to treat those around them like human beings,
and to refrain from bullying behaviour, harrassment or discrimination.

For additional info see https://www.freedesktop.org/wiki/CodeOfConduct

